Configuration.DescriptionLong: Payload Summary provides a simple summary of loading behaviour over the defined time period. Allows supervisors to monitor loading performance.
Productivity Rate demonstrates the tonnes per hourly period moved over a given time range. This widget is useful for identifying production inconsistencies between crews.
Availability demonstrates available time as a percentage of total Calendar time.
Use of Availability demonstrates utilised time as a percentage of available time.
Operating Efficiency demonstrates operating time as a percentage of utilised time.
Average Payload demonstrates the payload of the haul fleet for the time period selected.
Total Material Moved demonstrates the total material moved for the site over time.
Utilisation demonstrates utilised time as a percentage of calendar time.
Mean Time Between Failures is used to measure how reliable the equipment is.
Mean Time To Repair is used to quantify the turnaround time for the restoration of an equipment breakdown.
Total Cycles shows the total amount of cycles performed by a truck in a given time period.
Time Utilisation demonstrates a breakdown of time events for selected equipment.
Payload Distribution shows the loading behaviour over the selected time period. Useful to identify good loading practices and instances of overloading.
Pass Count Distribution demonstrates the pass count commonly required when loading. Useful to identify when loading units are failing to achieve appropriate bucket fill factors.
Map displays the geographical related information available from the site.
Payload Record Summary shows the 500 most recent load records for the selected time range.
Excavator Operator Performance provides a summary of each excavator operator's performance in the selected time period.
Truck Operator Performance provides a summary of each truck operator's performance in the selected time period.
Dozer Operator Performance provides a summary of each dozer operator's performance in the selected time period.
Excavator Waiting Time demonstrates the current average queue time at each loading unit in operation. Allows supervisors to make real time decisions on truck cycle allocations.
Excavator Productivity demonstrates the current productivity of each loading unit in operation. Allows supervisors to make real time decisions on truck cycle allocations.
Day First/Last Load displays the first and last load of each day shift in the selected time period.
Night First/Last Load displays the first and last load of each night shift in the selected time period.
Material Network shows the flow of material through the network.
Haul Cycle Status displays the current live status for haul cycles performance.
Asset Communication Status displays the current asset communication status.
Asset Status displays the current asset status.
Downtime Record Summary shows the 500 most recent downtime event records.
Excavator Dig Rate shows the dig rate of each excavator.

Supervisor Summary shows summary performance for key assets. Total Delay Time is the sum of automatic waiting activities and operating delays. Total Down Time is the sum of down time events input by operators.
Mine Information displays information about active grades, dumps, and blasts.
Excavator Current Blasts & Materials displays active blasts and materials for each excavator.
Current SMU displays the most current avaiable SMU reading for each asset.
SMU Reading displays the SMU reading for each asset for the selected time period.
Downtime Hours Pareto displays down time events as an ordered series of categories.
This filter allows the user to filter between two dates from multiple datasets (interval AND discrete)

This filter provides a way to filter datasets by the Region dimension.
This filter provides a way to filter datasets by the Structure Type dimension.
